{"questionId":"32719279","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the total number of revolutions that the Ferris wheel has made. Give your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mi>k</mi></msup></math> where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>10</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> is an integer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> (revolutions per hour) seen&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>32</mn></math> (revolutions per day) seen<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3000</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>96000</mn></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32719279","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ1.2e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the total number of revolutions that the Ferris wheel has made. Give your answer in the form a×10k where 1≤a<10 and k is an integer.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.1—Using standard form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}